Minister of Small Business Development Khumbudzo Ntshavheni. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has appointed Minister of Small Business Development Khumbudzo Ntshavheni as acting Minister in The Presidency. This follows the death last week of Jackson Mthembu from COVID-19 complications. READ: Jackson Mthembu: 'A man who loved his God' Ntshavheni will continue her duties.